==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*flōra-''.  Cognate with Middle Low German [[vlor|vlōr]] (Dutch [[vloer]] ‘floor’), Old High German [[fluor]] (German [[Flur]] ‘meadow, corridor, hall’), Old Norse [[flórr]] (Swedish ''flor'' ‘floor of a stable’).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /flo:r/

===Noun===
'''flōr''' ''f'' (''pl'' '''flōra''' or '''flōre''')
# the [[floor]] or [[ground]]

[[Category:Old English nouns]]

